cs.CR, cs.HC, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.SE

The paper focuses on the cybersecurity concerns of Brain Computer Interfaces (BCIs), which involves both computer security (cs.CR) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also discusses the potential risks and attacks that could affect BCIs, which falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CY). Additionally, the paper reviews the existing architectural versions of the BCI life-cycle and proposes a new approach, which could be classified under software engineering (cs.SE) and system integration (cs.SI).
